.SH BUGS
.IP \(bu 4
The
.B exit
built-in ignores any argument; it always exits with the previous command's
status rather than a user-supplied code.
.IP \(bu 4
.B split_string
allocates the token array with no bounds check on the count; a pathologically
long command line with many tokens could exhaust memory silently.
.IP \(bu 4
.B pathfinder
uses
.BR strtok (3),
which modifies a copy of PATH but is non-reentrant; concurrent or nested
calls would produce undefined behaviour.
